# Polizeiliche Kriminalstatistik\n\n*Die.EN-GB:
# Police crime statistics

*This dashboard provides an insight into the police crime statistics (PKS), which are published annually by the Federal Criminal Police Office (BKA).
*In it, certain offences or groups of offences are assigned 6-digit keys, and each year there are figures on how many offences per key were registered and solved.

The upper part is used to select the key: On the left, you can browse through the thematically organised keys or search for keys.
For the selection of keys that are currently visible on the inner ring or as a search result, the years in which the PKS published data for these keys are shown on the right.
Clicking on the coloured timeline of a key ensures that it is selected for viewing further down.
Up to four keys can be compared with each other.
Where a year of a key is marked in white on the right, this means that something has changed in its designation.
This may concern spelling or the content and thus possibly the comparability between the years.

Die folgende Zeitreihe zeigt für die aus.EN-GB:
The following time series shows for the selected keys how often offences under these keys have been committed over the years and how successful they have been in being solved.

Different keys vary greatly in their frequency, from one to seven digits.
In this graphic, you can zoom in with the mouse by dragging a rectangle.
Double-clicking on the plot background resets the zoom level.
Clicking on a bar removes it from the selection and the "Clear" button does the same for all keys.
Further options are also available at the top right of the graphic, e.g. moving back and forth or exporting as an image file.

Die zweite Zeitreihe zeigt die Entwicklu.EN-GB:
The second time series shows the development in the number of reported offences in a comparison of the federal states.
The y-axis here is the number of offences per 100,000 inhabitants in order to level out the difference in size between the federal states.

The national average is selected first, and clicking on the country abbreviations below the chart selects and deselects countries.
The same zoom and pan options are available here.
A double-click helps to quickly select and deselect all countries.

Bitte beachten, dass die Vergleichbarkei.EN-GB:
Please note that comparability between years is not always guaranteed, even without a change of name.
The definition of the keys can change from year to year, as can the punishability of various offences.
The question of whether the values of a key are comparable between two years (i.e. whether the conditions under which an offence is recorded under this key have not changed) is ultimately always determined by the catalogue of offences published with each PCS.
